latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Full thoughts on each product ⬇️ ⁣
⁣
Zoto’s low lather cleanser + conditioner - great option for a weekly wash day combo. Gets hair clean but doesn’t feel stripping 8/10 would definitely purchase ⁣
⁣
The Inkey List Oat Cleansing Bomb - I know this is a crowd favorite but I didn’t like that if felt like I had left over residue on my face after washing I it off 5/10 won’t repurchase ⁣
⁣
Tree Hut Shea Sugar Scrub: The fragrance was wayyy too strong for me. It made my eyes water in the shower. I feel like there are a lot better body scrubs out there 0/10 won’t repurchase ⁣
⁣
Amika The Kure Intense Bond Repair Mask: Such a good product! My hair felt strengthened and soft at the same time after using. 10/10 will repurchase ⁣
⁣
Briogeo Don’t Despair, Repair Deep Conditioning Mask: Super moisturizing and such a high quality deep conditioner 10/10 will repurchase ⁣
⁣
Authentic Beauty Concept Glow Mask: This is my 2nd container of this mask & it is such a good treatment if you have colored hair! 10/10 will repurchase ⁣
⁣
Aussie Frizz Taming Cream: I wanted this to work for my hair so bad but the mineral oil leaves my hair feeling greasy on day 1. 5/10 won’t repurchase ⁣
⁣
Aussie Instant Freeze Gel: Good affordable option for a strong hold gel. I use this for the last day before washday for slick buns. Can flake it you touch your hair too much 7/10 not sure if I’ll repurchase ⁣
⁣

latestPosts.caption:
I went in for a trim last week & this is what I asked for⤵️

My ends were starting to feel stringy so I had about 1 inch trimmed off from my length 

I asked to bring my layers up higher because I was starting to get a triangle shape🔺 bringing up your layers is how you can create more of a round, blended shape🌳 

My face framing had grown out quite a bit too, so I had those trimmed, and the shortest fringe start around my eyelashes and tapper down to blend in with the rest of my hair 

Oh and all of this done on wet hair! I alternate between wet & dry cuts. I get dry cuts if we are changing the shape of my hair so we can see how it’s going to lay but if I’m just going in for a trim, I prefer wet cuts! 

Let me know if you have any questions!!✂️

#curlyhair #curlycut #curlylayers #curlyhaircommunity #haircutformen #curlsforthegirls

My honest first impression of the Rizos Curls Strong Hold Gel

She’s thick but she gives a ton of hold!! I think this is a great gel if you’re looking for a very long lasting hold. 

The overall texture wasn’t my favorite since I prefer a thinner/runny gel formula but I’ll play around with emulsifying it next time 

If you have a hard time getting a gel cast, this might be the product for you. 

Overall I really liked my end results and will definitely be reaching for this on washdays that I want lots of definition and shine or when I need to lock my slick back styles into place!
